{"schema": {"fields":[{"type":"integer","name":"index"},{"type":"string","name":"author_association"},{"type":"string","name":"body"},{"type":"datetime","name":"created_at"},{"type":"string","name":"html_url"},{"type":"integer","name":"id"},{"type":"string","name":"issue_url"},{"type":"string","name":"node_id"},{"type":"datetime","name":"updated_at"},{"type":"string","name":"url"},{"type":"string","name":"user"}],"pandas_version":"0.20.0","primaryKey":["index"]}, "data": [{"index":0,"author_association":"OWNER","body":"\/ping @hoch","created_at":"2017-06-10T01:06:15.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/11133#issuecomment-307532034","id":307532034,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11133","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMwNzUzMjAzNA==","updated_at":"2017-06-10T01:06:15.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/307532034","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/97088?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk3MDg4","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mrdoob","type":"User","id":97088,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/orgs"}},{"index":1,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"@hoch @mrdoob\r\nThe issue is that I get a flutter\/tremolo effect where the audio is not panning smoothly when using setValueAtTime() as you can here in the example.\r\n\r\nSetting the value directly on the audioParam seems to fix it. Not sure why.\r\n\r\n(I'm testing with Chrome 59.0.3071.86)","created_at":"2017-06-12T12:19:12.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/11133#issuecomment-307772882","id":307772882,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11133","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMwNzc3Mjg4Mg==","updated_at":"2017-06-12T12:19:12.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/307772882","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/andreasplan8\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/andreasplan8\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/2635254?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/andreasplan8","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/andreasplan8\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/andreasplan8","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/andreasplan8\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI2MzUyNTQ=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/andreasplan8\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/andreasplan8\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/andreasplan8\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"andreasplan8","type":"User","id":2635254,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/andreasplan8\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/andreasplan8\/orgs"}},{"index":2,"author_association":"NONE","body":"@andreasplan8 \r\n\r\n> flutter\/tremolo\r\n\r\nThis means you're changing the parameter value too fast. The parameter setter (=) in Chrome implicitly applies smoothing (leaky integration or dezipper) over the certain time constant, so those modulation artifacts are smoothed out.\r\n\r\nSince the implicit smoothing is actually [deprecated from the spec](https:\/\/github.com\/WebAudio\/web-audio-api\/pull\/393), I recommend to use the automation method. For example,\r\n\r\n```js\r\n\/\/ To smooth parameter value over the frame-to-frame interval at 60fps.\r\nconst tau = 60\/1000;\r\nconst later = this.context.currentTime + tau;\r\n\r\nlistener.positionX.linearRampToValueAtTime(position.x, later);\r\nlistener.positionY.linearRampToValueAtTime(position.y, later);\r\nlistener.positionZ.linearRampToValueAtTime(position.z, later);\r\n```\r\n\r\nMore typing, but future-proof.","created_at":"2017-06-12T18:44:42.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/11133#issuecomment-307882420","id":307882420,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11133","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMwNzg4MjQyMA==","updated_at":"2017-06-12T18:44:42.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/307882420","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars1.githubusercontent.com\/u\/676891?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/hoch","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjY3Njg5MQ==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"hoch","type":"User","id":676891,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/orgs"}},{"index":3,"author_association":"OWNER","body":"> ```js\r\n> const tau = 60\/1000;\r\n> ```\r\n\r\nHardcoding this is probably not a good idea?","created_at":"2017-06-12T18:52:07.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/11133#issuecomment-307884695","id":307884695,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11133","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMwNzg4NDY5NQ==","updated_at":"2017-06-12T18:52:07.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/307884695","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/97088?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk3MDg4","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mrdoob","type":"User","id":97088,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/orgs"}},{"index":4,"author_association":"NONE","body":"Yeah, my code was just an example. If you have a variable that keeps the frame interval, it is probably good enough.\r\n\r\nOr you can calculate it from the time stamp from rAF() call?","created_at":"2017-06-12T19:18:55.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/11133#issuecomment-307892211","id":307892211,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11133","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMwNzg5MjIxMQ==","updated_at":"2017-06-12T19:19:33.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issu