stead of scheduling it? ","created_at":"2017-06-20T08:27:31.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/11133#issuecomment-309682042","id":309682042,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11133","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMwOTY4MjA0Mg==","updated_at":"2017-06-20T08:27:31.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/309682042","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/andreasplan8\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/andreasplan8\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/2635254?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/andreasplan8","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/andreasplan8\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/andreasplan8","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/andreasplan8\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI2MzUyNTQ=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/andreasplan8\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/andreasplan8\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/andreasplan8\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"andreasplan8","type":"User","id":2635254,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/andreasplan8\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/andreasplan8\/orgs"}},{"index":8,"author_association":"NONE","body":"@andreasplan8 It depends on the interval of setting values. If the interval is too coarse, then you'll hear glitches. Also I think what we want here is a smoothing transition between coordinates, thus the linear ramping makes sense. Chrome does the internal interpolation when the setter is used,  which is very similar to the code example above in terms of its behavior, but that is a non-compliant to the spec.","created_at":"2017-06-20T17:26:43.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/11133#issuecomment-309829859","id":309829859,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11133","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDMwOTgyOTg1OQ==","updated_at":"2017-06-20T17:26:43.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/309829859","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars1.githubusercontent.com\/u\/676891?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/hoch","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjY3Njg5MQ==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"hoch","type":"User","id":676891,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/orgs"}},{"index":9,"author_association":"NONE","body":"@mrdoob Someone needs to pick this up? Or should we just close?","created_at":"2018-05-16T19:49:50.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/11133#issuecomment-389643863","id":389643863,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11133","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM4OTY0Mzg2Mw==","updated_at":"2018-05-16T19:49:50.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/389643863","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars1.githubusercontent.com\/u\/676891?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/hoch","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjY3Njg5MQ==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"hoch","type":"User","id":676891,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/orgs"}},{"index":10,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"I would like to work on this if there is room for improvement. At the moment, `three.js`  updates the transformation of panner nodes like this:\r\n\r\nhttps:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/blob\/1476110de2e1eb55a77f4a6ff9ae443f4117566e\/src\/audio\/PositionalAudio.js#L112-L113\r\n\r\nAnd this is the code for `AudioListener`:\r\n\r\nhttps:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/blob\/1476110de2e1eb55a77f4a6ff9ae443f4117566e\/src\/audio\/AudioListener.js#L110-L127\r\n\r\nI have tested this setup multiple times in different browsers with `three.js`s web audio examples and it seems to work. Is this approach the recommended way? If not, what would be the ideal solution?","created_at":"2018-06-27T14:15:03.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/11133#issuecomment-400687284","id":400687284,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11133","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQwMDY4NzI4NA==","updated_at":"2018-06-27T20:06:06.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/400687284","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/12612165?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/Mugen87","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEyNjEyMTY1","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"Mugen87","type":"User","id":12612165,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/orgs"}},{"index":11,"author_association":"NONE","body":"In Chrome, using `setPosition()` and using `position{X,Y,X}.setValueAtTime()` are internally identical. So I wouldn't bother to hand-roll the method as shown above. Also I suspect that Chrome is the only browser that implemented AudioParam in PannerNode.\r\n\r\nOne thing to think about is: Chrome now does not do the internal smoothing between position. If you want to smooth the transition you'll have to use `linearRampToValueAtTime()` or the other automation methods. So if the transition is too fast, the audio might end up with glitches. This is true theoretically, but I have not seen any bug report on it yet.\r\n\r\nI think simply using `setPosition` and `setOrientation` might be good enough until all the browsers have the support for AudioParams in PannerNode.","created_at":"2018-06-27T18:11:06.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/11133#issuecomment-400778738","id":400778738,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11133","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQwMDc3ODczOA==","updated_at":"2018-06-27T18:11:06.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/400778738","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars1.githubusercontent.com\/u\/676891?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/hoch","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjY3Njg5MQ==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"hoch","type":"User","id":676891,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/hoch\/orgs"}},{"index":12,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"Many thanks for the information!\r\n\r\n> If you want to smooth the transition you'll have to use linearRampToValueAtTime() or the other automation methods. \r\n\r\nWould it be okay to use `setTargetAtTime()` and a constant value for the parameter `timeConstant`? `three.js` does this already at different place e.g. for adjusting gain values:\r\n\r\nhttps:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/blob\/1476110de2e1eb55a77f4a6ff9ae443f4117566e\/src\/audio\/AudioListener.js#L85\r\n\r\nWe did not find a nice solution so far in order to pass the real frametime to the audio entities. I guess this is one reasons why we are not using `linearRampToValueAtTime()` yet.","created_at":"2018-06-27T20:21:12.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/11133#issuecomment-400815949","id":400815949,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/11133","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDQwMDgxNTk0OQ==","updated_at":"2018-06-27T20:21:12.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/c